page.title: 02Ecology,Stiffkey coastland.
page.content: {Saltmarsh}(part of largest in Europe) {and sands with creeks}declared area of Special Scientific Interest.Owned partly by National Trust, partly by Nature Conservancy, the Crown, local land-owners. {Rare flora:}samphire, sea pinks, sea lavender, seablite. {Fauna:}migrants e.g. Brent Goose, drift migrants, waders; cockles, small fish, mussels, shrimps, worms, occasional seals; rabbits, birds in {'Greens'}(i.e. higher grass, bramble, gorse). {Drained marshland:} pasture. {Downland}(glacial debris): rough grazing; arable; in trimmed hedges and trees rare flora: Alexanders, yellow figwort.{Cockthorpe Common:}steep chalk bank rich in downland flora including orchid.
